## üë§ Profiles in Salesforce

- Define basic permissions for users.
- Every user has exactly one profile.

### Controls:
| Area               | Description                                      |
|--------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| Object Access      | View, create, edit, delete records               |
| Field-Level Access | Show/hide specific fields                        |
| Tab/App Access     | Control visibility in UI                         |
| Record Types       | Specify available types                          |
| Page Layouts       | Assign layouts                                   |
| Login Restrictions | Set login hours and IP ranges                    |

---

## üßæ Fields in Salesforce

- Define data structure within objects.
- Can be standard or custom.

### Common Field Types:
| Type                   | Description                                  |
|------------------------|----------------------------------------------|
| Text, Number, Currency | Basic data types                             |
| Date/Time              | Stores date and time                         |
| Checkbox               | Boolean value                                |
| Picklist               | Dropdown options                             |
| Lookup/Master-Detail   | Relationships between objects                |
| Formula                | Calculated values                            |
| Roll-Up Summary        | Aggregated child record data                 |

### Creating a Field:
1. Go to **Object Manager** ‚Üí Select Object.
2. Click **Fields & Relationships** ‚Üí **New**.
3. Choose field type and fill in details.
4. Set field-level security and layout visibility.
5. Save.

---

## üß† Best Practices Summary

- Use standard objects when possible.
- Create custom objects only when necessary.
- Always create tabs for objects that users need to access.
- Assign least privilege via profiles.
- Use permission sets for additional access.
- Add help text and validation rules to fields.
- Test changes in sandbox before deploying.
